{"title":"Santa Cruz Tweaks 5th-gen Bronson All-Mountain Bike with a Lower, Better VPP","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2024-santa-cruz-bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updated/","date":1724137260000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6987-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"Santa Cruz Bronson, Chamonix, France 2024\" /></p>\n<p>A new Santa Cruz Bronson promises to be better than ever with subtle updates you’d have to look hard to notice. Still 150/160mm of do-it-all travel, but with more balanced mullet geometry and a tweaked VPP suspension layout that moves its link forward for a smoother ride. Santa Cruz refined their popular carbon all-mountain bike, creating an even better trail bike <em>AND</em> a more capable big mountain shredder…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The California bikemakers’s most-popular all-rounder is the mountain bike for riders who want one bike for blasting local singletrack loops, heading out into the backcountry for all-day trail rides, and dropping into the bikepark for a taste of enduro. The platform has been a solid all-mountain performer for <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/santa-cruz-bronson-juliana-roubion-stretch-150mm-of-enduro-all-mountain-bike-from-trail-to-park/\" target=\"_blank\">more than 8 years</a>, getting a mullet update <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mixes-wheel-sizes-for-the-best-of-both-worlds/\" target=\"_blank\">in 2022</a>, and internal frame storage <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/interview-pro-bike-check-nina-hoffmann-and-her-santa-cruz-bronson-training-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">the next year</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_kalimotxo_profile_desktop-edited-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/Santa Cruz)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now it gets “evolved MX geometry” and an “<em>even better VPP</em>“. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1467\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated VPP suspension\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_001-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This is the 5th generation Bronson. And honestly, it looks a lot like gens 3 &amp; 4. OK, the new split spars at the bottom of the seattube do actually set this one apart. But it’s really the subtle forward shift of the VPP links that redefine how this bike rides – with a more plush feel and improved traction to soak up the tougher trails mountain bikers are riding these days.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s new?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1466\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike, riding Chamonix, FR\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_1459-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>“When you can only have one bike, and your mission is to ride that bike into oblivion then this is the one. From manicured bike parks to blown out loamy berms, alpine lines to backyard trails, the Bronson is as at home in the air as it is in the dirt.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout.jpg\" alt=\"New gen 5 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updates, better VPP\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_new-VPP-layout-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Santa Cruz reconfigured the long-running layout of the Bronson’s VPP (<em>virtual pivot point</em>) suspension that has defined this all-rounder since 2013. By moving the key lower link forward and the main pivot slightly down, Santa Cruz say they’ve lowered the bike’s anti-squat. The result is a more supple bike that can soak up the big bumps even when you are standing on the pedals and filter out trail chatter even when you are pedaling.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph.jpg\" alt=\"New gen 5 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updates, anti-squat comparison\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_anti-sqaut-graph-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Santa Cruz call it all-around better VPP performance for a better all-rounder bike </p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote>\n<p>“Reduced pedal kickback on square-edge hits. Remains active while pedaling up and across rough, technical terrain. Less anti-squat benefits descending sensitivity due to the reduced pedal kickback associate.”</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n\n\n<h3>Evolved MX Geometry </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1466\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated, riding Chamonix\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0359-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Santa Cruz Bronson is still a 150mm mullet trail bike, paring the smaller 27.5″ rear wheel to 160mm of travel up front and a larger 29″ front wheel. Santa Cruz insist mullet is the way to go for this playful shredder style bike. It benefits from the more agile rear end and more stable front, and a neutral feel “when pointed downhill”. But Santa Cruz also say the mullet setup gives them more freedom to play with rear end length for a more balanced ride. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry.jpg\" alt=\"New gen 5 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updates, geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updates_Bronson-5-geometry-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>So now the Bronson gets size-specific chainstays. And it gets proportional geometry across the 5-size range (S-XXL) with even slacker angles. Now the Bronson gets a 63.9° or 64.2° head angle and 77.3-78.4° effective seat angle, depending on whether you pick the LOw or HIgh position at the rear shock mount flip-chip.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In a time of ever-growing frame Reach, the same-size Bronsons aren’t actually longer. But the 27.5-only XS is gone and they add the new XXL at the other end of the spectrum.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike, frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-297x167.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-1536x864.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-120x68.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-768x432.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-2048x1152.jpeg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_FactoryFLoatX_FrameOnly_Kalimotxo-edited-1200x675.jpeg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Glovebox secure internal frame storage in the downtube under the bottle cage mount</li>\n\n\n\n<li>enclosed fully-guided internal cable routing from the sides of the headtube</li>\n\n\n\n<li>C carbon frames are compatible with mechanical shifting</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CC carbon frames only include internal routing for a rear brake &amp; dropper post – wireless electronic shift-only</li>\n\n\n\n<li>2.5″ max tire clearance, front &amp; rear </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Boost 148mm spacing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Post Mount brakes with 200mm front /180mm rear rotors</li>\n\n\n\n<li>ISCG05 chain guide mounts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>BSA Threaded bottom bracket</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Santa Cruz UDH</li>\n\n\n\n<li>IS 1.5″ tapered headset</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Lifetime frame warranty</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easy-to-source, easy-to-service bearings</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated, headtube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_009-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated, post mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_005-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated, drivetrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_002-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updatedlinkage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_006-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-1536x1024.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike, glovebox\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_Details_012-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>2024 Santa Cruz Bronson – Options &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1466\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike, big mountain in the French Alps\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_M3_0893-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Bronson now comes in two colors – Kalimotxo pink and Root Beer brown – and in 5 complete bike build options. Or as a $3900 frameset. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1050\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec.jpg\" alt=\"New gen 5 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updates, 2024 spec\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec-297x156.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec-1536x806.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec-120x63.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/New-gen-5-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike_2024-Spec-768x403.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Three builds – a $5000 / 5500€ R, $5900 / 6400€ S &amp; the $7000 / 7400€ GX AXS get the more affordable C carbon frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_R_Kalimotxo-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>2024 Santa Cruz Bronson C R</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_S_TranslucentRootBeer-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Bronson C S</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_C_GX_AXS_Kalimotxo-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Bronson C GX AXS</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>While the top two $8000 / 8800€ X0 AXS &amp; $9000 / 10k€ X0 AXS RSV specs get the top-tier CC carbon frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_TranslucentRootBeer-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>2024 Santa Cruz Bronson CC XO AXS</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-scaled.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1152\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-1536x1152.jpeg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike updated\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/MY25_Bronson_CC_X0_AXS_RSV_Kalimotxo-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Bronson CC X0 AXS RSV</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As for spec updates, those top 3 new SRAM AXS bikes also get Maven brakes, all but the entry build get Fox 36 forks and Float X rear shocks. And all bikes get all-mountain-ready Maxxis Assegai + DHR II tire combos.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1466\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Santa Cruz Bronson carbon all-mountain bike&lt; BAAW\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Bronson_K4A6855-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Word is that the Bronson’s Juliana Roubion sister bike won’t be getting the same updates, at least for the time being. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\">SantaCruzBicycles.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2024-santa-cruz-bronson-carbon-all-mountain-bike-updated/\">Santa Cruz Tweaks 5th-gen Bronson All-Mountain Bike with a Lower, Better VPP</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"55eda61e5ad44554e144a77b95315fb1685168245711d9ff188589c581621b17","category":"Cycling"}